  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0dc6\u0dca\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dad \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc2\u0dd3\u0dba \u0d86\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0daf\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China ready to provide more humanitarian aid to Afghanistan",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Chinese Premier and Foreign Minister Wang Yi has said that China is ready to provide more timely assistance to Afghanistan based on China's needs, and hopes that the country will be united in rebuilding its homes as soon as possible to recover from the recent earthquake disaster.",
        "He made the remarks during a telephone conversation with Amir Khan Mutaki, acting Foreign Minister of the Interim Government of Afghanistan.",
        "Wang again expressed condolences to Afghanistan over the quake, saying that China, as a friendly neighbor and sincere friend, has been working with the Afghan people during difficult times.",
        "He said various Chinese agencies, from central and local governments to social organizations and enterprises, were continuing to work to provide emergency humanitarian assistance to Afghanistan and to assist the Afghan people.",
        "According to Wang, the first group will provide tents, blankets and other supplies by special aircraft, while cash and other relief supplies will be delivered to Afghanistan as soon as possible."
      ],
